The paper deals with network coding schemes for sending multiple sources over a general noisy network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses compress-forward coding and decoding techniques for interference channels, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves coding and decoding algorithms, which can be categorized under data structures (cs.DS).
